qOriginalFields.desc:
Is shown for fixed records.
qOriginalFieldName and qName are identical if no field names are used in the file.
qOriginalFieldName differs from qName if embedded file names are used in the file.

qHasNull.desc: This property is set to true if the field contains some Null values.

qHasDuplicates.desc: This property is set to true if the field contains some duplicate values.

qIsSynthetic.desc: This property is set to true if the field contains a synthetic key.

qInformationDensity.desc:
Number of records that have values (i.e. not NULL) in the field as compared to the total
number of records in the table.

qnNonNulls.desc: Number of values that are non Null.

qnRows.desc: Number of rows in the field

qSubsetRatio.desc:
Number of distinct values in the field (in the current table) as compared to the total
number of distinct values of this field (in all tables).

qnTotalDistinctValues.desc: Number of distinct values in the field.

qKeyType.desc: Tells if the field is a key field.

qTags.desc: List of tags related to the field.
